<subSubSection lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="303" pageId="7" pageNumber="302" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,763,1960,2079]" lastBlockId="8.[151,761,1501,1684]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="303" pageId="7" pageNumber="302">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,271,1960,1983]" pageId="7" pageNumber="302">Comment.</emphasis>
The genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Fieber, 1870" authorityName="Fieber" authorityYear="1870" box="[397,667,1960,1983]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Platycranus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="302" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[397,526,1960,1983]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="302">Platycranus</emphasis>
Fieber, 1870
</taxonomicName>
consists of green and broad headed species which are strictly associated with 
<taxonomicName box="[283,366,2024,2047]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Genista" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="7" pageNumber="302" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[283,366,2024,2047]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="302">Genista</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp. In Turkish fauna, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fieber" authorityYear="1870" box="[630,759,2024,2047]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Platycranus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="302" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[630,759,2024,2047]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="302">Platycranus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is represented by five species: 
<taxonomicName authority="Fieber, 1870" authorityName="Fieber" authorityYear="1870" box="[487,727,2056,2079]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Platycranus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="302" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erberi">
<emphasis box="[487,580,2056,2079]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="302">P. erberi</emphasis>
Fieber, 1870
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Reuter, 1879" authorityName="Reuter" authorityYear="1879" box="[740,1039,1740,2079]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Platycranus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="302" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="putoni">
<emphasis box="[740,896,1740,2079]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="302">P. putoni</emphasis>
Reuter, 1879
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Wagner, 1955" authorityName="Wagner" authorityYear="1955" box="[1048,1313,1740,1763]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Platycranus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="302" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="remanei">
<emphasis box="[1048,1159,1740,1763]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="302">P. remanei</emphasis>
Wagner, 1955
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Lindberg, 1948" authorityName="Lindberg" authorityYear="1948" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Platycranus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="302" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="genistae">
<emphasis box="[1323,1436,1740,1763]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="302">P. genistae</emphasis>
Lindberg, 1948
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Douglas &amp; Scott, 1868) (ONDER et al. 2006)" baseAuthorityName="Douglas &amp; Scott" baseAuthorityYear="1868" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Compsidolon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="302" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicolor">
<emphasis box="[1055,1160,1772,1795]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="302">P. bicolor</emphasis>
(Douglas &amp; Scott, 1868) (
<bibRefCitation author="ONDER F. &amp; KARSAVURAN Y. &amp; TEZCAN S." box="[836,1030,1804,1827]" pageId="7" pageNumber="302" refId="ref9968" refString="ONDER F., KARSAVURAN Y., TEZCAN S. &amp; FENT M 2006: Heteroptera (Insecta) Catalogue of Turkey. Ege Universitesi Ziraat Fakultesi, Izmir, vi + 164." type="book" year="2006">ÖNDER et al. 2006</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. While the first two species belong to the subgenus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fieber" authorityYear="1870" box="[978,1107,1836,1859]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Platycranus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="302" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">
<emphasis box="[978,1107,1836,1859]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="302">Platycranus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1116,1177,1836,1859]" pageId="7" pageNumber="302" sensu="stricto">s. str.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, the other three species belong to the subgenus 
<taxonomicName authority="Wagner, 1956" authorityName="Wagner" authorityYear="1956" box="[1067,1368,1868,1891]" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Platycranus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="302" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Genistocapsus">
<emphasis box="[1067,1220,1868,1891]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="302">Genistocapsus</emphasis>
Wagner, 1956
</taxonomicName>
which is identified by the long labium reaching at least the middle coxae (KNYSHOV &amp; KONSTANTINOV 2013). 
<taxonomicName authority="Linnavuori, 1999" authorityName="Linnavuori" authorityYear="1999" class="Insecta" family="Miridae" genus="Platycranus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="302" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="alkestis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="302">Platycranus alkestis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="LINNAVUORI R. E. &amp; MODARRES M." box="[892,1076,1964,1987]" pageId="7" pageNumber="302" pagination="215 - 231" refId="ref9472" refString="LINNAVUORI R. E. &amp; MODARRES M. 1999: Studies on the Heteroptera of the Khorasan province in N. E. Iran. II. Cimicomorpha: Miridae. Entomologica Fennica 10: 215 - 231." type="journal article" year="1999">Lınnavuori, 1999</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
was originally described from the island of Rhodes and was known only from its 
<typeStatus box="[1307,1352,1996,2019]" pageId="7" pageNumber="302">type</typeStatus>
locality up to now. This species can be distinguished from other species of its subgenus by relatively long first antennal segment (0.7× as long as width of head) and brown colored pronotum and scutellum (KNYSHOV &amp; KONSTANTINOV 2013). The specimens we examined have paler coloration with scutellum being pale brown and pronotum being yellowish to green (
<figureCitation box="[252,339,1629,1652]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="7.[151,182,1635,1654]" captionTargetBox="[164,1436,200,1603]" captionTargetId="figure-18@7.[151,1437,186,1620]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="Fig. 4. A‒B ‒ Maurodactylus kukuensis V. G. Putshkov, 1978: A ‒ male; B ‒ female. C ‒ Pinalitus viscicola (Puton, 1888), male. D ‒ Platycranus (Genistocapsus) alkestis Linnavuori, 1999, male. Scale bars: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4489000" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4489000/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="303">Fig. 4D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
